column1: Rule 5: Modifiers with multiple fluorine atoms, such as perfluorinated chains, tend to result in a low yield.
column2: Rule 6: Modifiers with formyl groups (-CHO) attached to an aromatic ring tend to result in a low yield.
column3: Rule 7: Modifiers with a methoxy group (-OCH3) in combination with a carboxylic acid group tend to result in a low yield.
column4: Rule 12: Modifiers with a long aliphatic chain (more than 6 carbons) and an amino group (-NH2) tend to result in a low yield.
